## servicio-producto
This project is a microservice API for managing product information, interacting with an external product API.

## Structure
servicio-producto/
├── index.js # Application entry point.
├── cliente.html # HTML file served for client interaction.
├── package.json
├── package-lock.json
└── .env # File for environment variables (e.g. API_KEY).

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:

   git clone https://github.com/Cristina-Colcha/app-tienda.git
   cd servicio-producto
2. Install dependencies:

   npm install
3. Set up environment variables:

Create a .env file in the root directory of the project and add any necessary environment variables, such as API keys.

API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY
## Execution
Once installed and configured, you can start the server:

   node servidor.js
The service will be accessible at http://localhost:4003.

## API Endpoints
GET /products: Retrieves all products from an external API.
GET /products/:id: Retrieves a specific product by ID.
PUT /products/:id: Updates a product by ID.

